author: dlr
msg: * subversion/libsvn_wc/copy.c
(svn_wc_copy2): Add the destination's repository to the error
message used when the source and destination repository URIs are
different.

author: djh
msg: Handle new versions of neon in the Windows build.
* build/generator/gen_win.py
(WinGeneratorBase.parse_options): Add a default neon version number.
(WinGeneratorBase.__init__): Call _find_neon when needed.
(WinGeneratorBase._find_neon): New method to find neon version number.
(WinGeneratorBase.get_win_defines): If neon is new enough, define
SVN_NEON_0_25.

author: cmpilato
msg: Restore authz callback functionality (that is, when no callback is
provided at all) to the SWIG Python bindings.
* subversion/bindings/swig/python/libsvn_swig_py/swigutil_py.c
(svn_swig_py_repos_authz_func): Move the setting of the default
return value up above the first place the function can return, so
that if not real authz callback is provided, "allowed" isn't left
unset.  This was inadvertantly broken in r15848.

author: cmpilato
msg: Fix a nasty SEGFAULT that could occur when folks use a non-absolute FS
path as input to svn_repos_trace_node_locations.
* subversion/libsvn_repos/rev_hunt.c
(svn_repos_trace_node_locations): Ensure that the input FS path is absolute.
* subversion/tests/libsvn_repos/repos-test.c
(node_locations): Repeat the test, using the non-absolute FS path form.

author: kfogel
msg: Use a string instead of an enum to describe filesystem back end types.
This cooperates better with third-party fs implementations.
Suggested by: dlr
(From his review of r16162.)
* subversion/include/svn_fs.h
(SVN_FS_CONFIG_FS_TYPE): Adjust comment.
(svn_fs_fs_type_t): Remove this enum group.  [I meant to remove this
enum group, but only removed its doc string instead!  See r16197.]
(svn_fs_type): Change prototype and redocument.
* subversion/libsvn_fs/fs-loader.h
(struct svn_fs_t): Change 'type' field to a constant string.
* subversion/libsvn_fs/fs-loader.c
(svn_fs_new): Initialize fs->type to NULL.
(svn_fs_type): Adjust prototype.
* subversion/libsvn_fs_fs/fs.c
(fs_create, fs_open): Yow!  Change an int to a string by upcasing.
* subversion/libsvn_fs_base/fs.c
(base_create, base_open): Change an int to a string by upcasing.  Yow!
